The paper focuses on conversational machine reading comprehension, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel graph neural network model, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The model also involves temporal dependencies, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions visualization experiments, which could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
